This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with understanding driving scenes using sensors. It also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it discusses training algorithms for driver behavior detection. Robotics (cs.RO) is another likely sub-category as the research involves an instrumented vehicle. Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is also a possible sub-category as the paper discusses learning driver behavior. Finally, human-computer interaction (cs.HC) is a possible sub-category as the research involves understanding how humans interact with traffic scenes.
